fetter.detail: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

0.name: Normal Attack: Foreign Ironwind
0.description:
<color=#FFD780FF>Normal Attack</color>
Performs up to 5 rapid strikes.

<color=#FFD780FF>Charged Attack</color>
Consumes a certain amount of Stamina to unleash 2 rapid sword strikes.

<color=#FFD780FF>Plunging Attack</color>
Plunges from mid-air to strike the ground below, damaging opponents along the path and dealing AoE DMG upon impact.

1.name: Palm Vortex
1.description: Grasping the wind's might, you form a vortex of vacuum in your palm, causing continuous Anemo DMG to opponents in front of you. The vacuum vortex explodes when the skill duration ends, causing a greater amount of Anemo DMG over a larger area. Hold DMG and AoE will gradually increase. Elemental Absorption If the vortex comes into contact with Hydro/Pyro/Cryo/Electro, it will deal additional elemental DMG of that type. Elemental Absorption may only occur once per use. You discussed the way to grasp the formless wind with Paimon.

3.name: Gust Surge
3.description: Guiding the path of the wind currents, you summon a forward-moving tornado that pulls objects and opponents towards itself, dealing continuous Anemo DMG. Elemental Absorption If the tornado comes into contact with Hydro/Pyro/Cryo/Electro, it will deal additional elemental DMG of that type. Elemental Absorption may only occur once per use. You and Paimon studied the flapping of a butterfly's wings.

4.name: Slitting Wind
4.description: The last hit of a Normal Attack combo unleashes a wind blade, dealing 60% of ATK as <color=#80FFD7FF>Anemo DMG</color> to all opponents in its path.

5.name: Second Wind
5.description: <color=#FFD780FF>Palm Vortex</color> kills regenerate 2% HP for 5s.\nThis effect can only occur once every 5s.

0.name: Raging Vortex
0.description: <color=#FFD780FF>Palm Vortex</color> pulls in opponents and objects within a 5m radius.

2.name: Sweeping Gust
2.description: Increases the Level of <color=#FFD780FF>Gust Surge</color> by 3.\nMaximum upgrade level is 15.

3.name: Cherishing Breezes
3.description: Reduces DMG taken while casting <color=#FFD780FF>Palm Vortex</color> by 10%.

4.name: Vortex Stellaris
4.description: Increases the Level of <color=#FFD780FF>Palm Vortex</color> by 3.\nMaximum upgrade level is 15.

5.name: Intertwined Winds
5.description: Targets who take DMG from <color=#FFD780FF>Gust Surge</color> have their <color=#80FFD7FF>Anemo RES</color> decreased by 20%.\nIf an Elemental Absorption occurred, then their RES towards the corresponding Element is also decreased by 20%.
